In 2001, President Bush banned federal funding for embryonic stem cell research due to ethical concerns.
However, California voters recently approved funding for this controversial research, aiming to make the state a global hub for stem cell studies.
Meanwhile, a study on Parkinson's disease revealed how dopamine levels affect learning abilities in patients.
Actor Michael J.
Fox, who has Parkinson's, supports stem cell research and campaigned for John Kerry.
Additionally, researchers made a breakthrough in understanding Huntington's disease, suggesting potential cures from embryonic stem cell research.
A gene mutation linked to Parkinson's was also discovered by an international research team.
